
4 Tbsp canola oil
1 Tbsp whole cumin seeds
9 cloves garlic (crushed) (approx. 3 tbsp)
14 oz can crushed tomatoes
2 tbsp fresh grated ginger
2 tbsp ground coriander
1 tsp turmeric
1 tsp sea salt
1/2 tsp cayenne pepper
4 cups water
1 cup mung beans, well rinsed
14 oz can coconut milk
1-2 medium limes, juiced
1/2 cup fresh cilantro, choppped

 1) Heat cooking oil over medium high head.
 2) Add cumin seeds and cook for 60 seconds.
 3) Add garlic, saute 3-4 minutes until browned.

 4) Add crushed tomatoes and stir.
 5) Add ginger, coriander, turmeric, salt, cayenne
 6) Saute 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

 7) Add water and mung beans.
 8) Increase heat to high and bring to boil.
 9) Reduce to low, cover, and simmer approx. 30 minutes,
    stirring once or twice.

10) When done, stir in coconut milk.
11) Increase heat to meidum high.
12) When it comes to a boil, turn off the heat.
13) Stir in cliantro and lime juice to taste.

